metadata.description: ISP-GIN ablation study: isolating complex interference contribution

mathematical_notes.isp_nomp_magnitude: |exp(i*theta)| = 1 for all theta. ISP-NoMP magnitude-based should distinguish EXACTLY 0 pairs — this proves message passing (interference) is essential, not just initialization.
mathematical_notes.isp_nomp_phases: Phases = omega * f(v) mod 2pi. Equivalent to testing if sorted node feature values alone can distinguish graphs. Gives ISP-NoMP a fairer chance than magnitude-based version.
mathematical_notes.wl_expected: All pairs are 1-WL equivalent by construction. WL should distinguish 0 pairs. Any WL success indicates a data bug.
